parameters:
Clea: Please tell us about the reason why we were locked up,
as well as the problem.

Village Chief Olden: This mountain is called Mount Scrilo.
It is said that dragons used to live here.

Village Chief Olden: The villagers, who were frightened by
the ferocious dragons, offered food to appease their anger.

Village Chief Olden: However, the anger of the dragons did
not subside, so according to the ancient legend, we decided
to offer the village's shrine maiden as a sacrifice.
Thief Nora: Eek... I-Is this... a folktale?

Village Chief Olden: Nevertheless, animals frightened by the
dragons' periodic outbursts of anger would seek refuge in
the village.

Village Chief Olden: Eventually, the village's food ran out
and the warriors suffered serious injuries from repeated
battles. That's why--

Priestess Sophia: So, we reached out to the Adventurer's
Guild, and it seems like this is a recent story.
Thief Nora: S-So, so, there really are dragons!?

Priestess Sophia: Clea's story was true. Dragons definitely
exist.

Mage Relm: It's true... Dragons are not just legends, they
actually exist in this mountain...!

Clea: Why a sacrifice? We could have asked the Empire for
help.

Village Chief Olden: It is the village's rule!! We have
something that we must protect even at the cost of our
lives.

Village Chief Olden: For that reason, the village... I
offered my own daughter as a sacrifice to the dragon!!
Village Chief Olden: Guh...! What are you doing, let go...!!

Clea: Isn't it a father's duty to protect his daughter!? My
father was like that, he challenged the dragon for my sake!!

Clea: Even though he knew he couldn't win, he stood up
against that monster all by himself!!

Clea: You, who offered your own daughter, have no right to
call yourself a father...!!
Priestess Sophia: Clea-chan, could you let go?
Clea: I will go defeat the dragon. Please wait here.

Village Chief Olden: Stop, it's impossible! I just want you
to come as a combatant for the Adventurer's Guild!

Clea: I have lived until today for the purpose of defeating
it. Now that I know its whereabouts, I absolutely cannot
turn back.

Priestess Sophia: If we don't come back, please contact the
Adventurer's Guild for us.
Village Chief Olden: ...Tsk... You fools... Phoni... I...
